Executive Profile
Saul A. Fox J.D.Executive Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Fox Paine, Global Indemnity LimitedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 21 different industries.See Board Relationships63$1,106,992
Background

		Mr. Saul A. Fox, J.D., has been the Chief Executive at Fox Paine & Company, LLC since 1996 and also serves as its Founder, Founding Member and Director. Mr. Fox served as the Chief Executive Officer at United America Indemnity Ltd. from February 9, 2007 to June 2007. From 1984 to 1997, he was at Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. (KKR). He served as a Senior General Partner at KKR and was responsible for three of its exceptionally successful transactions, American Reinsurance, ... Canadian General and Motel 6. During his 13 years with KKR, Mr. Fox led a focused investment effort in the global insurance and reinsurance sectors. This effort included the 1992 acquisition of American Reinsurance Corp. and the 1995 acquisition of Canadian General Insurance Company. Prior to joining Kohlberg, Kravis & Roberts & Co., he was employed at Latham & Watkins. Mr. Fox was an Attorney specializing in tax, business law and mergers and acquisitions and participated significantly in law firm management at Latham & Watkins LLP. There, he built a national legal practice structuring complex business transactions. He was also an active participant in Latham & Watkins' management and administration. Over the course of his 30 year career in private equity, Mr. Fox orchestrated numerous corporate acquisitions in such areas as consumer products, energy, independent power generation, information technology, lodging, medical instruments, reinsurance and specialty property and casualty insurance. Mr. Fox has been an Executive Chairman at Global Indemnity Limited (formerly, Global Indemnity plc) since September 5, 2003. He serves as the Chairman of ACMI Corporation. He serves as the Chairman of L'artisan Parfumeur S.a. and Cradle Holdings, Inc. He has been an Executive Director of Global Indemnity Limited since August 2003. Mr. Fox has been a Director of Wind River Insurance Co. (Barbados) Ltd. since August 2003 and Wind River Insurance Co. (Bermuda) Ltd. since October 2003. He has been a Director of Wind River Services Ltd. since October 2003. Mr. Fox serves as a Director of American Forest Products; American Reinsurance Company Inc.; American Cystoscope Manufacturers, Inc.; Byram Healthcare Centers Inc.; Ref-Fuel, Inc.; Canadian General Insurance Group Limited; ACMI Circon Holdings Corp.; Layne Inc.; The Marley Company, LLC; Victoria Reinsurance Co.; Covanta ARC Holdings, Inc.; Paradigm Geotechnology B.V.; Paradigm Geophysical, Ltd.; Erno Laszlo, Inc.; Penhaligon's Ltd.; and Jean Laporte L’Artisan Parfurmeur S.A. He has been a Director of Seminis Inc. since September 2003 and Alaska Communications Systems Holdings Inc. since May 1999. He is a Member of the Board of Overseers of the University of Pennsylvania Law School. He served as the Chairman of Paradigm B.V. since September 2006. He served as the Chairman of Gyrus ACMI, Inc. Mr. Fox served as a Director of WJ Communications Inc. since January 2000 and VCST Industrial Products n.v. He served as a Director of Maxxim Medical Inc. since November 1999 and Alaska Communications Systems Group Inc. since 1999. Mr. Fox served as the Chairman of Medical Wind Down Holdings I Inc. since July 2000. He served as the Chairman of the Board of Medline Industries, Inc. since July, 2000. Mr. Fox served as a Director of Medline Industries, Inc. since November, 2000 and was a Director of Fred Meyer Inc., Motel 6 Inc., General Accident Group (Canada) Ltd., Union Texas Petroleum Holdings Inc., and United American Energy Corp. He served as Director of Paradigm Ltd. He is a recipient of the Temple University Distinguished Leadership Award. Mr. Fox received a J.D., cum laude, from the University of Pennsylvania Law School in 1978. In 1975, he received a B.S. in Communications and Computer Science, summa cum laude, from Temple University, where Mr. Fox was the President's Scholar in 1975.Read Full Background




