daging the stump where Mr. Fox's tail once was, when they heard the ground crumbling above them. Mr. and Mrs. Fox gathered their four children and started digging as fast as they could. They dug a deep hole, and stayed there all night.Boggis, Bunce, and Bean realized that manual shovels were not going to get the job done quickly, so they went to get the mechanical shovels.-meanwhile-Climax continuedBoggis, Bunce, and Bean started to dig out Mr. Fox. By the end of the day, the hill was a crater. All the foxes dug furiously until they could dig no more. As the sun went down, the farmers sent for tents and food (and cider for Bean). They also sent for  the men that worked on their farms. The men would surround the hill and stand guard during the night with a gun and a flashlight, with orders to shoot the fox.Also, Boggis, Bunce, and Bean vowed that they would not leave the crater until they shot Mr. Fox dead8-29-147th GradeFalling ActionMrs. Fox was weak, she could no longer dig. So the children and Mr. Fox set out on an adventure. They dug and dug and dug, then went to the surface, and they were under Boggis' Chicken House Number One. They grabbed 3 plump chickens, and one of the children took it to Mrs. Fox to roast.Boggis, Bunce, and Bean still waited for Mr. Fox to come out.Falling Action continuedAfter Mr. Fox stole from Boggis, he was digging another tunnel with the remaining three children when suddenly, they heard a voice. Then out of the tunnel came Mr. Badger and his son. Mr. Badger said that every animal in the forest was starving, and that they needed food. Mr. Badger's son went to tell all the animals of the forest that they were invited to Mr. Fox's feast, while Mr. Fox, his children, and Mr. Badger snuck into Bunce's Giant Storehouse. They stole 4 ducks, 3 geese, 3 hams, and 10 bunches of carrots for the rabbits.Bunce's Giant StorehouseBoggis's Chicken House Number OneDiggingDiggingFalling Action  continued Bean's Secret Cider CellarAfter Mr. Fox stole from Boggis and Bunce, he went with Mr. Badger and his remmaining child to Bean's Secret Cider Cellar.  They dug into the cellar and found a rat, sipping one of the cider jugs. Mr. Fox threatened to eat him and the rat left. They were about to get a jug of cider of a shelf when they heard footsteps. They hid behind  jug of cider. They saw a hand take the two jugs of cider that were right beside them, then the hand was on the jug of cider they were behind, but then the person opted not to and went back upstaris. Mr. Fox, his kid, and Mr. Badger grabbed 3 jugs of cider and went back to the hole.ResolutionThe FeastWhen Mr. Fox came back, all the animals were already eating. Mr. Fox then gave a speech. He said that all the animals would live in an underground community and build streets and homes and steal from all the farmers until they were all dead. All the animals celebrated Fantastic Mr. Fox.As for Boggis, Bunce, and Bean, they are still waiting for Mr. Fox to come out of the hole.MoralThe Moral of this story is that if you keep doing the same thing and waiting for something new to happen, nothing new will ever happen. This is demonstrated by Boggis, Bunce, and Bean. They kept digging instead of trying something else and were outsmarted by Mr. Fox. This means to try something new and you will be successful.Personal RecomendationI would not recommend this book to people. Overall the book wasn't that exciting or emotional. It was a bit dull and boring. The plot was original, though. I liked the book, but didn't love it.The EndAbout the BookFantastic Mr. Fox was written by Roald Dahl. The book was published in 1970. The movie version was released in theaters in 2009 and Full transcriptMore presentations by
    
        
